step 3:Creating KPIs ,Pie chart ,area chart

In the following section we will see showing the domestic and non-domestic crimes in pie chart

 First, we will create a new sheet

To create a new sheet, go to the navigation and select app overview

Then click create new sheet button and give it appropriate name and description




Then double click and open it and it will show empty sheet and click edit to load  data and make analysis


Then drag and drop pie chart 


Then use domestic as dimension by clicking on the dimension and use count(ID) as measure.


In the foot note write ‘true indicates Domestic and false  Non domestic’


Click the chart and edit the title as Domestic vs non domestic


Now drag and drop two filter pane and use zip code and police districts as a dimension

To change the style and the color of the pie chart

Go to appearance and under the presentation choose donut style


then click done and see what the result look like

In the following section on the same sheet ,  we will use KPI to show the percentage of false arrest and the average arrest in each zip code

First, we will create variables. to create variables go to the left bottom corner and click ‘x’ icon

Then click create  new button and give appropriate name and description for the variable and close


Write this expression to the definition of vFalseArrest:   count({<Arrest={'false'}>}ID)



Create a variable for total arrest the same way and total zip codes the same way with the following codes respectively: count({<Arrest=>}ID) , count(distinct([Zip Codes]))

then we can see the three variables created:



In order to create the percentage of the false arrest we will use KPI.

Drag and drop KPI to the sheet and  use the following code as a measure for the KPI (Note that KPI only takes measures):

left(($(vFalseArrest)/$(vTotalArrest)*100) ,2)& '%'



                              then name it as % of false arrest



In order to conditionally color the KPI, go to the appearance then  color, disable the library  coloring and add limits and choose appropriate coloring  and signs for each limit by selecting each limit one by one


By clicking Add limit we can add as many limits as we want


Do the coloring for the remaining limits like the above

Then finaly the KPI will look like this
